> "He's a short, human male, 23 years old, with a dark brown haircut shaped like an upside-down bowl."

**[Thorin]** — *reacting to the bowl cut description*
> "His mom put a bowl on his head and then cut around the—"

---

**[GM]** — *establishing the timeline via Tadric*
> "Janussi was found dead by great reader A'lai Aivenmore and the servant, Miss Hollypocket, around 7.30 in the morning, and the two of them raised the alarm."

**[Thorin]** — *pressing for more detail*
> "Did they discover… did they discover him together, or did somebody discover him first? Do we know?"

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "I arrived at the crime scene with the gate warden around 8 AM, so for all I know, yes, they did."

**[Thorin]**
> "So we're gonna have to interview them."

**[GM]** — *continuing Tadric's timeline*
> "Then a little bit later, Kazryn Nyantani arrived distraught and weeply, shortly after 8 AM, wanting to see the body of Janussi. Which she did, but only from the doorway. Then, Fheminor Scrivenbark stern up at 8.30, appearing shocked. She wanted to inspect the chamber, but it was… rules had already been set, nobody was allowed to go in. Then Bookward showed up at 9 from the baths, having been alerted to the situation. As Acting Head of Candlekeep, she was allowed to enter the chamber, but took a brief only look at the scene before confirming the garden warden's order not to admit anyone. And the gate warden returned at 11 to make a full investigation. He seemed careful not to sully the crime scene in any way before he left to make his report to the Council of Great Readers."

**[Thorin]** — *about the gate warden's inspection*
> "Did it look like he discovered something?"

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "He definitely looked more determined after he walked out."

**[Zalthir]** — *pressing Tadric on whether he watched the gate warden inside*
> "Did he touch anything whatsoever?"

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "Well, he seemed careful not to sully the crime scene."

**[Zalthir]**
> "Granted, but did you touch anything whatsoever?"

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "Not that I noticed."

**[Zalthir]**
> "Were you watching carefully?"

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "No, my job was to make sure nobody came in, not so much to look inside."

