**[GM]** — *elaborating on the wound*
> "The keeper's rib cage was smashed by what appears to be an axe, or similar, using several precise blows, all very close to one another. And you also notice that while the keeper of the tome's vestments are covered in blood and… Cruds. The mest is surprisingly localized around the wound. As someone who has killed more than his fair share of people, you're very… it's like he… you would have expected spurting jets of blood to have covered not only more of his robes, but also more of the room."

**[Thorin]** — *key deduction*
> "The question, was he dead before his heart was hacked out?"

**[GM]** — *Grygum's clerical insight, delivered OOC*
> "because Grygum is a cleric, he immediately realizes what's going on, was Zalthir is speculating about the deaths. He goes, oh! you can't raise the dead of somebody if the vital organs are not there."

**[Zalthir]**
> "I was gonna ask about that, okay."

**[GM]**
> "So, somebody decided to steal his heart to make Raise Dead impossible."

