**[Speak with Dead — Already Cast?]**

**[Thorin]** — *proposing an alternative*
> "Is there any way that we can commune with the dead, even though they don't have all their parts? I mean, we don't need the heart, we just need the brain to be able to talk to him, you know."

**[GM]** — *as Tadric*
> "yes, we did try to speak with the dead, but apparently the dead were not speaking."

**[Zalthir]**
> "Huh?"

**[Daz]**
> "How can that happen?"

**[Thorin]** — *identifying who may have tried*
> "Wait, who tried when? The, like, City Watch guy or whatever that got fired, did he try and, like, speak with the dead?"

**[GM]**
> "Yes."

**[Thorin]**
> "Gotta interview that dude."

**[GM]** — *explaining the spell's restriction*
> "Speak with Dead grants a semblance of life and intelligence to a corpse of your choice within range, allowing it to answer the questions you pose. The corpse must still have a mouth and can't be undead. The spell fails if the corpse is the target of the spell within the last 10 days."

**[Zalthir]**
> "Oh, so someone cast it already."

**[GM]**
> "Perhaps."

**[Thorin]** — *asking about the ten-day window*
> "So if we wait 10 days, then we can cast it again?"

**[GM]**
> "Yes."

**[Thorin]**
> "Corpse will be a little stinky by then."

**[GM]**
> "Yes."

**[Thorin]**
> "Is there any ice around?"

**[GM]** — *ending the session*
> "Alright, we will stop here."
